SUMMARY:LGBTQIA2S+ Youth & Allies Summit
DESCRIPTION:The LGBTQIA2S+ Youth & Allies Summit is a day of connection\, empowerment\, and celebration for queer and gender-diverse youth across Alaska—and the allies who uplift them. Hosted by The Queen’s Guard\, this gathering centers joy\, safety\, education\, and solidarity in a space designed to honor lived experience\, build community\, and spark action.\nThrough workshops\, performances\, resource sharing\, and affirming dialogue\, participants will explore identity\, advocacy\, and creative resistance. Whether you’re navigating your own journey or showing up in support\, the Summit offers tools\, inspiration\, and belonging.\nThis is more than an event—it’s a launchpad for leadership\, healing\, and unapologetic pride.\n\nPalmer Train Depot\n610 S Valley Way\, Palmer\, AK
URL:https://visitpalmer.com/event/lgbtqia2s-youth-allies-summit/
END:VEVENT
